video_title: Why You Struggle To Set Boundaries?
transcript:
when you need to set a boundary and say
no but it feels uncomfortable to do that
you might notice that you go into
people-pleasing mode and you start to
over-explain why you can't do something
this happens when you believe that your
own health is not a good enough reason
to disappoint other people
but all that over explaining yourself
chips away at your self-confidence
because it reconfirms your belief that
other people need to buy into those
reasons for them to be valid
